original: Eriksson, Knut Gösta, leg. läkare, Borås, f. M/S/13 i Härnösand av Per A. E. o. Margareta Olsson. G. 46 m. Monica Larsson. — Stud :ex. i Härnösand 32, med. kand. i Lund 37, med. lic. 45. Tf. andre läk. v. SMsjöns sjukhus 43, 44, e. prov :läk. i Harads 44, i Gamlehy 45, tf. prov :läk. v. Solhems sjukhus i Borås sed. 46. Hob-bies: fiske, filateli.
translated: Eriksson, Knut Gösta, licensed physician, from Borås. Born on May 13th, in Härnösand to parents Per A. E. and Margareta Olsson. Married to Monica Larsson in 1946. He received his high school diploma in Härnösand in 1932, his Bachelor of Medicine in Lund in 1937, and his medical license in 1945. He served as a deputy physician at SMsjöns Hospital in 1943 and 1944, as a probationary doctor in Harads in 1944 and in Gamlehy in 1945, and as a deputy probationary doctor at Solhems Hospital in Borås since 1946. His hobbies include fishing and philately.
